<article id="node-16739">
<h1 >3.6.7.175 Bereavement Provisions for CA</h1>
<h2>Death of a child with a disability</h2>
<p>A person receiving <a href="../../../acronyms#ca" title="Carer allowance">CA</a> (child) may qualify for a CA bereavement payment upon the death of the child for whom they had caring responsibilities.</p>
<p>A 14 week bereavement payment is payable from the date of the child's death when, immediately before the child's death, the child was an <a href="../../../acronyms#ftb" title="Family tax benefit">FTB</a> child (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/2/1/1">2.1.1</a>) of the person in receipt of CA (child). This is paid as a lump sum.</p>
<p>Where, immediately before the child's death, the child was NOT an FTB child of the person in receipt of CA (child), the person may be qualified for CA for 4 weeks from the date of the child's death.</p>
<p>This applies also on the death of a child who did not, on their own, qualify the carer for CA (child), but who qualified the carer because of the combined scores under the <a href="../../../acronyms#dcla" title="Disability Care Load Assessment">DCLA</a> (<a href="../../../1/1/d/170">1.1.D.170</a>) of 2 children.</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> The carer does not have to be in receipt of FTB payments for the child to meet the FTB child definition.</p>
<h2>Death of an adult with a disability</h2>
<p>A person receiving CA (adult) may qualify for a CA bereavement payment upon the death of the disabled adult for whom they had caring responsibilities.</p>
<p>A 14 week bereavement payment is payable from the date of the disabled adult's death in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul><li>the carer was in receipt of CA (adult) for the care of a disabled adult on the day the disabled adult died,</li>
<li>the carer was also receiving an income support payment (other than <a href="../../../acronyms#cp" title="Carer payment">CP</a>) on the day the disabled adult died, AND</li>
<li>the carer did not otherwise qualify for a bereavement payment because of their receipt of an income support payment (under the SSAct or <a href="../../../acronyms#vea" title="Veterans' Entitlements Act 1986">VEA</a>).</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 23(1)-'income support payment', section 992J Continued carer allowance during bereavement rate continuation period where disabled child dies, section 992K Lump sum payable in some circumstances (death of disabled child), section 992L Continuation of qualification for carer allowance for 4 weeks in some cases where recipient's disabled child dies, section 992LA Continued carer allowance during bereavement rate continuation period where disabled adult dies, section 992LB Lump sum payable in some circumstances (death of disabled adult)</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../../1/5">3.1.5</a> Bereavement Payment Provisions</p>
<p>FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/2/2">2.2</a> FTB Eligibility for Individuals</p>
</div>
